33:44.370 --> 33:46.633
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

34:00.168 --> 34:03.911
ANDERS:
Fallon, I know you can do this.

34:03.954 --> 34:06.261
I've been aware of
how special you are

34:06.305 --> 34:08.872
since you could first walk.

34:08.916 --> 34:11.614
I'm proud of you, as always.

34:11.658 --> 34:13.225
Anders.

34:23.670 --> 34:26.760
On a scale of one to ten,
how much do you hate me?

34:26.803 --> 34:27.978
Ten being I should start running

34:28.022 --> 34:29.371
before you throw a Manolo
at my head.

34:29.415 --> 34:31.330
I'm not upset with you at all.

34:31.373 --> 34:33.071
Really?

34:33.114 --> 34:35.943
From what I can remember,
about last night,

34:35.986 --> 34:37.988
which is not a lot,
thank God,

34:38.032 --> 34:39.338
Paloma was furious.

34:39.381 --> 34:40.730
And everyone knows
if you piss her off

34:40.774 --> 34:41.731
you're as good as dead.

34:41.775 --> 34:43.211
I don't care about Paloma.

34:43.255 --> 34:44.865
I care about you.

34:44.908 --> 34:47.128
I just wanted
you to be okay

34:47.172 --> 34:50.000
because...

34:50.044 --> 34:53.830
if you were okay,
then maybe I could be, too.

34:53.874 --> 34:56.181
You're not okay?

34:57.878 --> 34:59.314
I thought I was.

34:59.358 --> 35:04.232
But, well, turns out
I needed an ugly cry, too.

35:04.276 --> 35:05.712
[chuckles]

35:05.755 --> 35:07.192
Aren't ugly cries
the best sometimes?

35:09.063 --> 35:11.326
The truth is...

35:11.370 --> 35:15.025
I feel guilty
that your father died

35:15.069 --> 35:16.288
on the day he saved my life.

35:16.331 --> 35:18.203
I mean, he must have
been exhausted.

35:18.246 --> 35:20.683
What if that had something to do
with the crash?

35:20.727 --> 35:23.164
Get that thought out
of your head right now. Okay?

35:23.208 --> 35:25.775
He loved you,
and he would save you again,

35:25.819 --> 35:26.994
even with the same outcome.

35:28.387 --> 35:29.779
Thank you, Kirby.

35:29.823 --> 35:32.304
Now, go get dressed.

35:32.347 --> 35:34.044
We have to go somewhere.

35:36.743 --> 35:39.137
NOLAN:
So you want to send
a rocket into space?

35:39.180 --> 35:42.183
Yes. And I want to build it
so it can be manned.

35:42.227 --> 35:44.272
Now I see why
you needed Korosh,

35:44.316 --> 35:46.405
because of his background
in frozen fuels,

35:46.448 --> 35:48.842
which your ex-wife
obviously told you

35:48.885 --> 35:52.237
was my company's focus after
our date a couple weeks ago.

35:52.280 --> 35:54.717
Look, man, you won
fair and square.

35:54.761 --> 35:56.763
I just wanted you to know

35:56.806 --> 35:58.895
it's not a game to me.

35:58.939 --> 36:01.071
I'm looking to make an impact
on the world.

36:01.115 --> 36:03.726
Why didn't you tell me this
in the first place?

36:03.770 --> 36:05.467
I don't like sending ideas
out into the world

36:05.511 --> 36:06.816
until they're ready.

36:06.860 --> 36:09.254
I get that.

36:09.297 --> 36:10.777
And if anyone can do this,

36:10.820 --> 36:12.257
it's you.
Besides,

36:12.300 --> 36:14.041
someone needs
to shut Elon Musk up.

36:14.084 --> 36:16.130
[both laugh]

36:16.174 --> 36:17.740
Hey, why don't you join me, huh?

36:17.784 --> 36:19.960
Two billionaires are
better than one.

36:20.003 --> 36:21.875
Thanks, I'll pass.

36:21.918 --> 36:24.225
I enjoyed the competition,
but I don't need Korosh,

36:24.269 --> 36:25.879
and clearly you do.

36:25.922 --> 36:27.272
So what's the next step?

36:27.315 --> 36:30.100
I head to Washington
and ask Congress for funding.

36:30.144 --> 36:31.754
You're gonna hear a lot of noes.

36:31.798 --> 36:33.408
Then I'll fund it myself.

36:33.452 --> 36:34.931
Be careful.

36:34.975 --> 36:37.325
There were times
when I was building my company

36:37.369 --> 36:40.285
that I had two weeks before
I completely ran out of money.

36:40.328 --> 36:43.505
Actually, that was when
things were most fun.

36:43.549 --> 36:44.898
[chuckles]

36:44.941 --> 36:47.248
But put something away offshore,
just in case.

36:47.292 --> 36:50.512
Oh, don't worry,
I got it covered.

36:50.556 --> 36:52.471
I can't believe I did that.

36:52.514 --> 36:54.124
So now what?

36:54.168 --> 36:57.215
Now I take a shower,
and never speak of the time

36:57.258 --> 36:59.478
I climbed into a dumpster again.

36:59.521 --> 37:01.044
Then I have to get this to Leo
without him knowing

37:01.088 --> 37:02.220
we ever had it.

37:02.263 --> 37:03.786
Why didn't we just
do that first?

37:03.830 --> 37:06.093
Because I've never had to deal
with a problem like this before.

37:06.136 --> 37:08.269
Geez.I need a drink.

37:12.534 --> 37:17.017
"Mr. Jones, a package for me
was delivered a few days ago

37:17.060 --> 37:19.193
to the club
instead of the hotel."

37:19.237 --> 37:20.455
What's that?

37:20.499 --> 37:22.022
It's a note from
your head chef.

37:22.065 --> 37:24.329
"Special cassava root flour.

37:24.372 --> 37:27.288
Packs of it."

37:27.332 --> 37:29.464
Which would look like...

37:29.508 --> 37:31.292
It was flour.

37:31.336 --> 37:33.120
Did I really just pack

37:33.163 --> 37:35.253
five to seven years' worth
of worry lines

37:35.296 --> 37:38.299
into two days
because of a box of flour?

37:38.343 --> 37:40.040
I ate a half a box of doughnuts.

37:41.215 --> 37:42.303
Okay, it was a whole box.

37:42.347 --> 37:43.826
Look, we need to do something.

37:43.870 --> 37:46.220
Even when he's not around,
the stress of having Leo

37:46.264 --> 37:47.482
in our lives is killing us.

37:47.526 --> 37:49.092
I know.

37:49.136 --> 37:51.225
I mean, seriously, look.
Is there a bald patch?

37:51.269 --> 37:53.445
[grunts][phone chimes, vibrates]

37:53.488 --> 37:56.274
Oh, I don't think
we have a choice.

37:56.317 --> 37:58.188
We need to get rid of Leo
once and for all,

37:58.232 --> 38:01.540
or he's gonna get rid of us.

38:06.893 --> 38:09.243
I like slowing things
down a little.
It's nice.

38:09.287 --> 38:10.984
Maybe next time we can have
breakfast in bed.

38:11.027 --> 38:14.204
Hold the breakfast.[phone chiming]

38:16.555 --> 38:18.034
Oh, it's my lawyer.

38:18.078 --> 38:20.254
Hang on, it'll only
take a second.

38:22.300 --> 38:24.606
Mitchell, talk to me.

38:24.650 --> 38:27.174
What? Indicted?
This is ridiculous.

38:27.217 --> 38:29.350
Actual jail time?

38:29.394 --> 38:31.526
Hey, hey, at the risk
of sounding insensitive,

38:31.570 --> 38:34.616
Garth and I had a deal pending.
Is that moving forward?

38:37.010 --> 38:39.447
What's wrong?

38:39.491 --> 38:41.362
Garth Wheeler.

38:41.406 --> 38:43.146
He's been indicted
for massive tax fraud.

38:43.190 --> 38:44.147
The deal's off.

38:44.191 --> 38:46.236
The land has been designated

38:46.280 --> 38:47.542
as protected parkland.

38:47.586 --> 38:51.329
Blake, I'm so sorry.
Maybe we can...

38:51.372 --> 38:52.895
Mitch says it's done.

38:52.939 --> 38:55.681
So you'll find land
in a different location.

38:55.724 --> 38:57.900
You'll build that airport.Location is everything.

38:57.944 --> 38:59.554
This location.

38:59.598 --> 39:03.384
This is my punishment
for doing things the right way.

39:03.428 --> 39:05.647
KIRBY:
This spot's so peaceful.

39:07.562 --> 39:09.390
My dad would like it.

39:10.826 --> 39:12.698
FALLON:
The trees remind me
of that weekend,

39:12.741 --> 39:14.613
you know, when we took
that camping trip

39:14.656 --> 39:16.528
with our Girl Scout troop.

39:16.571 --> 39:18.921
Anders had to step in
when my mother realized

39:18.965 --> 39:21.837
chaperoning meant
it would be a dry weekend.

39:21.881 --> 39:24.274
I remember.

39:24.318 --> 39:25.928
It was the first time
he had s'mores,

39:25.972 --> 39:28.191
and he loved them.
[sniffles]

39:28.235 --> 39:30.672
He always made them for me
when I had a bad day.

39:30.716 --> 39:33.545
He said s'mores can get you
through anything.

39:33.588 --> 39:37.375
Well, s'mores and
a pocketknife. [chuckles]

39:37.418 --> 39:41.727
He really was obsessed with us
learning survival skills.

39:41.770 --> 39:44.643
We got our merit
badges that weekend.

39:44.686 --> 39:46.645
He was so proud.

39:49.735 --> 39:51.301
I always thought
I'd have more time

39:51.345 --> 39:53.260
to make him proud again.

39:54.957 --> 39:57.395
I can't believe
I missed his funeral.

39:57.438 --> 40:00.441
I feel so guilty.

40:00.485 --> 40:02.661
Is that why
you've been drinking?

40:08.275 --> 40:10.973
I'm really sorry, Kirby.

40:11.017 --> 40:12.540
I guess I just didn't
want to face the fact

40:12.584 --> 40:13.541
that you were struggling.

40:13.585 --> 40:15.978
It's okay.

40:16.022 --> 40:19.286
I need to take responsibility,
too.

40:21.331 --> 40:22.289
Can I, uh...

40:22.332 --> 40:23.333
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Of course.

40:29.949 --> 40:32.299
[sniffles]

40:36.999 --> 40:39.872
You know, grief is
a useless emotion, Kirby.

40:44.398 --> 40:46.444
But I still feel it.

40:46.487 --> 40:48.489
There are no merit badges
for guilt.

40:48.533 --> 40:51.492
I could maybe get you one
for moving on

40:51.536 --> 40:52.928
and taking care of yourself.

40:52.972 --> 40:54.582
So you're not mad?

40:54.626 --> 40:56.454
Every time we have
an argument,

40:56.497 --> 40:58.499
we always come back
together again.

40:58.543 --> 41:00.719
This would have been the same.

41:00.762 --> 41:02.590
You'll always be my daughter.

41:02.634 --> 41:05.506
We just ran out of time
on this one.

41:07.334 --> 41:11.773
Now go live
a big, beautiful life.

41:11.817 --> 41:13.645
And get yourself
a pocketknife.

41:20.565 --> 41:22.349
[exhales, sniffles]

41:23.829 --> 41:26.309
Coming here was
exactly what I needed.

41:26.353 --> 41:29.791
But, um, I just need
to make one more stop.

41:29.835 --> 41:32.402
Rehab.

41:32.446 --> 41:34.100
I'm a mess.

41:40.846 --> 41:43.022
I'm sorry, you just weren't
performing up to my standards.

41:43.065 --> 41:45.024
I told you this would take time.

41:45.067 --> 41:46.808
Well, now it'll take
someone else's time.

41:46.852 --> 41:47.853
You're done here.

41:47.896 --> 41:49.681
We appreciate all of
your hard work,

41:49.724 --> 41:51.421
but that box
is gonna stay here.

41:51.465 --> 41:52.988
All of your research
and testing,

41:53.032 --> 41:56.383
that's property
of the hospital. Now...

41:59.038 --> 42:00.039
Oh, good luck in the future.

